headline: Woodward (WWD) Q1 Earnings and Revenues Surpass Estimates
summary: Woodward (WWD) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of +31.35% and +10.11%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Are New Aftermarket Acquisitions Altering The Investment Case For TransDigm Group (TDG)?
summary: In recent weeks, Wall Street analysts highlighted TransDigm Group’s acquisitions of Stellant Systems for US$960,000,000 and Jet Parts Engineering with Victor Sierra Aviation for US$2.20 billions as meaningful additions to its aerospace portfolio. Analysts also projected higher quarterly earnings per share and revenue, pointing to expected growth across TransDigm’s Power & Control and Airframe segments in both commercial and defense end-markets.
